parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to misfire, stall, or even fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. This can also cause damage to other engine components, such as catalytic converters, resulting in costly repairs and potential environmental hazards.

The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to emit excessive pollutants, leading to environmental hazards and potential health risks. It can also cause the engine to misfire, stall, or fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the control arm can cause the vehicle to swerve or lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle swerves or pulls to one side
the control arm is cracked or broken
the vehicle sags or leans to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air suspension system can cause the vehicle to sag or lose ride height, affecting its stability and control.
symptoms: The vehicle sags or leans to one side
the air shocks or compressor fail

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain can cause the engine to stall or hesitate, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Abnormal sounds coming from the engine compartment
squeaking noise when depressing the accelerator pedal
hesitation when attempting to accelerate to high speeds
